===Noun===

A [[Christian]] religious ceremony involving [[bread]] and [[wine]], blessing and remembrance. It is derived from the original [[Jewish]] ceremony of [[Seder]].

#A [[sacrament]] of [[Communion]] in the [[Christian]] church, (also named the [[Mass]] in the Roman Catholic denomination).
It is considered as one of the seven sacraments by the Roman Catholic and Eastern churches.

In some protestant denominations, called the [[Lord's Supper]],

From a [[greek]] word, signifying thanksgiving, appreciation.


